1
00:01:18,920 --> 00:01:22,020
- USS Kelvin, go for Starfleet base.
- Starfleet Base.

2
00:01:22,055 --> 00:01:23,820
We sent you a transmission.
Did you receive it?

3
00:01:24,020 --> 00:01:25,385
Kelvin, can you double-check those readings?

4
00:01:25,420 --> 00:01:28,120
Our gravitational sensors are going crazy
here. You should see this.

5
00:01:28,220 --> 00:01:29,620
It looks like a lightning storm.

6
00:01:29,720 --> 00:01:31,320
What you've sent us doesn't seem possible.

7
00:01:31,420 --> 00:01:33,520
Yes ma'am, I understand.
That's why we sent it.

8
00:01:34,120 --> 00:01:36,620
- Report.
- Still out of visual range. 20 seconds.

9
00:01:36,820 --> 00:01:41,020
Alert Captain Robau that Starfleet advised to
proceed with caution...

10
00:01:41,120 --> 00:01:42,485
Polarize the view screen.

11
00:01:42,520 --> 00:01:45,120
- Whatever this is... Klingon origin?
- Captain, we have visual.

12
00:01:45,220 --> 00:01:48,320
- Repeat. Could this be Klingon?
- Negative, lieutenant.

13
00:01:48,520 --> 00:01:50,320
You're 75000 kilometers
from the Klingon border.

14
00:01:50,355 --> 00:01:52,620
Captain, are you seeing this?

15
00:01:54,720 --> 00:01:56,620
My God.

16
00:02:16,920 --> 00:02:19,120
I have a reading.
They've locked weapons on us!

17
00:02:19,155 --> 00:02:20,220
Red alert!

18
00:02:20,320 --> 00:02:22,920
Torpedo locked on us at 320Â°- 2!
Arm weapons!

19
00:02:25,820 --> 00:02:27,320
Evasive pattern delta 5!

20
00:02:29,420 --> 00:02:30,820
Incoming! Fast!

21
00:02:36,620 --> 00:02:39,485
Fire all phasers!
Damage report.

22
00:02:39,520 --> 00:02:42,320
Warp drive's been knocked out.
Never seen anything like it.

23
00:02:43,620 --> 00:02:45,820
Weapons offline.
Main power at 38%.

24
00:02:45,920 --> 00:02:48,120
- They're firing another!
- All power to forward shields!

25
00:02:56,920 --> 00:02:58,820
Help me...

26
00:03:02,720 --> 00:03:05,020
...maneuver has been lost.

27
00:03:05,120 --> 00:03:06,085
Are shields even on?

28
00:03:06,120 --> 00:03:08,120
...decks 17 and 13, we have
confirmed casualties.

29
00:03:08,155 --> 00:03:10,720
11% and dropping. 10%.
Shields at 9% still dropping.

30
00:03:10,820 --> 00:03:12,820
All remaining power to forward shields.

31
00:03:13,020 --> 00:03:14,720
Prepare shuttles for evacuation.

32
00:03:17,220 --> 00:03:19,385
Hello.

33
00:03:19,420 --> 00:03:22,020
My commander requests the presence of
your captain

34
00:03:22,120 --> 00:03:24,620
in order to negotiate a ceasefire.

35
00:03:24,820 --> 00:03:30,220
You will come aboard our ship via shuttlecraft.
Your refusal would be unwise.

36
00:03:43,220 --> 00:03:45,620
Walk with me.

37
00:03:50,620 --> 00:03:53,820
If I don't report in 15 minutes
evacuate the crew.

38
00:03:54,020 --> 00:03:56,720
- Sir, we could...
- There is no outpost out here.

39
00:03:56,920 --> 00:04:00,520
Use autopilot and get off this ship.

40
00:04:00,620 --> 00:04:02,020
Aye, Captain.

41
00:04:02,120 --> 00:04:04,420
You're captain now, Mr. Kirk.

42
00:05:17,620 --> 00:05:20,220
His heart rate is elevated.

43
00:05:41,920 --> 00:05:43,820
Look at the ship.

44
00:05:45,120 --> 00:05:48,920
- Are you familiar with this craft?
- Who is your commander?

45
00:05:50,020 --> 00:05:53,020
- Is that him?
- I will speak for Captain Nero.

46
00:05:53,120 --> 00:05:58,920
Then ask Captain Nero:
What gives him the right to attack a Federation vessel?

47
00:06:11,520 --> 00:06:15,220
Do you know the location of
Ambassador Spock?

48
00:06:17,620 --> 00:06:20,420
I'm unfamiliar with
Ambassador Spock.

49
00:06:21,920 --> 00:06:25,020
- What is the current stardate?
- Stardate?

50
00:06:27,020 --> 00:06:29,420
2233.04.

51
00:06:31,520 --> 00:06:33,120
Where are you from?

52
00:06:39,220 --> 00:06:40,720
Terminated.

53
00:06:40,820 --> 00:06:42,620
- Sir, they have a lock on our signal.
- They're launching again.

54
00:06:42,655 --> 00:06:44,320
Bravo 6 maneuver fire, full spread!

55
00:06:55,520 --> 00:06:58,520
I'm initiating general order 13. We're evacuating!

56
00:06:58,555 --> 00:06:59,420
Yes sir.

57
00:07:04,220 --> 00:07:07,320
All decks, this is the Captain speaking.
Evacuate the ship immediately.

58
00:07:07,420 --> 00:07:09,585
Get to your designated shuttlecraft.
I repeat, begin evacuating...

59
00:07:09,620 --> 00:07:13,220
- That's George's voice. What's happening?
- We'll deliver it in the shuttle. Go!

60
00:07:26,220 --> 00:07:27,720
- George.
- You're OK, thank God.

61
00:07:27,820 --> 00:07:31,020
I have medical shuttle 37 standing by.
Get to it now. Can you do that?

62
00:07:31,055 --> 00:07:32,620
- Yes.
- Everything's gonna be OK.

63
00:07:32,720 --> 00:07:37,620
- Do exactly as I say, shuttle 37.
- George, it's coming.

64
00:07:38,420 --> 00:07:40,820
- Our baby. It's coming now.
- I'm on my way.

65
00:07:46,420 --> 00:07:50,920
Autopilot function has been destroyed.
Manual operation only.

66
00:07:52,020 --> 00:07:54,820
Clear those decks now! Get to the shuttles!
Move! Move! Move!

67
00:07:59,220 --> 00:08:02,020
- That was a big one!
- Just keep breathing. You'll be fine.

68
00:08:02,120 --> 00:08:05,120
- And the baby too, right?
- And the baby too.

69
00:08:10,320 --> 00:08:12,620
Right here.

70
00:08:16,820 --> 00:08:19,385
Captain to shuttle 37.
Is my wife on board?

71
00:08:19,420 --> 00:08:22,020
- Yes sir, she is.
- I need you to go now. Do you hear me?

72
00:08:22,120 --> 00:08:24,920
- We're waiting on you sir.
- No, just go, take off immediately.

73
00:08:25,420 --> 00:08:27,320
- That's an order.
- Yes sir.

74
00:08:27,355 --> 00:08:29,220
Wait. We cannot go yet.

75
00:08:31,820 --> 00:08:34,220
Please stop.

76
00:08:35,820 --> 00:08:39,120
George, the shuttle's leaving. Where are you?

77
00:08:39,420 --> 00:08:43,020
Sweetheart, listen to me.
I'm not gonna be there.

78
00:08:43,720 --> 00:08:45,720
- No.
- This is the only way you'll survive.

79
00:08:45,820 --> 00:08:48,620
Please don't stay on the ship. You have to be here.

80
00:08:48,720 --> 00:08:50,920
The shuttles will never make it if I don't
fight them off.

81
00:08:50,955 --> 00:08:53,820
George, I can't do this without you.

82
00:08:53,920 --> 00:08:56,320
OK, I need you to push now!

83
00:09:35,420 --> 00:09:37,820
SYSTEMS FAILING

84
00:09:42,720 --> 00:09:44,520
COLLISION COURSE
ENGAGED

85
00:10:14,120 --> 00:10:16,020
- What is it?
- It's a boy.

86
00:10:16,055 --> 00:10:16,920
A boy?

87
00:10:18,620 --> 00:10:23,120
- Tell me about him.
- He's beautiful.

88
00:10:24,820 --> 00:10:27,320
George, you should be here.

89
00:10:27,920 --> 00:10:30,220
Impact alert.

90
00:10:31,620 --> 00:10:35,220
- What are we gonna call him?
- We can name him after your father.

91
00:10:35,320 --> 00:10:38,620
Tiberius, you kiddin' me?
No, that's the worst.

92
00:10:40,620 --> 00:10:43,320
Let's name him after your dad.
Let's call him Jim.

93
00:10:45,620 --> 00:10:49,120
Jim. OK. Jim it is.

94
00:10:53,720 --> 00:10:55,920
- Sweetheart can you hear me?
- I can hear...

95
00:10:56,020 --> 00:10:57,620
I love you so much.

96
00:10:59,220 --> 00:11:00,320
I love you!

97
00:11:42,520 --> 00:11:53,320
STAR TREK

98
00:12:18,520 --> 00:12:21,020
Hey, are you out of your mind?
That car is an antique.

99
00:12:21,120 --> 00:12:23,320
You think you can get away with this
just because your mother's off planet.

100
00:12:23,420 --> 00:12:29,620
You get your ass back home now! You live in my
house buddy. You live in my house and that's my car.

101
00:12:29,720 --> 00:12:33,120
You get one scratch on that car
and I'm gonna whip your ass...

102
00:12:56,620 --> 00:12:59,320
Hey Johnny!

103
00:13:18,520 --> 00:13:20,920
Citizen, pull over.

104
00:13:47,420 --> 00:13:48,820
Noooo...!

105
00:14:14,720 --> 00:14:16,620
Is there a problem officer?

106
00:14:17,320 --> 00:14:19,620
Citizen, what is your name?

107
00:14:20,120 --> 00:14:23,020
My name is James Tiberius Kirk.

108
00:14:41,220 --> 00:14:45,620
- What is the formula for the volume of a sphere?
- 4/3 PI times the radius cubed...

109
00:14:46,520 --> 00:14:48,020
1.26...

110
00:14:58,120 --> 00:15:02,120
- What is the dimensionality...
- Dimensionality equals the logarithm of n divided by...

111
00:15:02,320 --> 00:15:04,220
...non-excludability and non-rivalry...

112
00:15:04,255 --> 00:15:06,220
...4/3 PI times the radius...

113
00:15:06,320 --> 00:15:09,120
...is morally praiseworthy
but not morally obligatory.

114
00:15:12,720 --> 00:15:14,320
Spock.

115
00:15:15,920 --> 00:15:19,220
I presume you've prepared new insults for today?

116
00:15:19,320 --> 00:15:21,620
Affirmative.

117
00:15:28,920 --> 00:15:32,720
This is your 35th attempt to illicit an emotional
response from me.

118
00:15:32,820 --> 00:15:35,520
You're neither Human nor Vulcan and
therefore have no place in this universe.

119
00:15:35,620 --> 00:15:38,720
Look, his Human eyes.
They look sad. Don't they.

120
00:15:38,920 --> 00:15:42,020
Perhaps an emotional response
requires physical stimulae.

121
00:15:44,020 --> 00:15:46,120
He's a traitor you know? Your father.

122
00:15:46,220 --> 00:15:48,920
For marrying her. That Human whore.

123
00:16:17,820 --> 00:16:20,320
They called you a traitor.

124
00:16:24,620 --> 00:16:27,420
Emotions run deep within our race.

125
00:16:27,520 --> 00:16:29,985
In many ways more deeply than in humans.

126
00:16:30,020 --> 00:16:33,820
Logic offers a serenity humans
seldom experience.

127
00:16:34,720 --> 00:16:39,420
The control of feelings...
so that they do not control you.

128
00:16:42,420 --> 00:16:46,020
You suggest that I should be completely Vulcan?

129
00:16:46,120 --> 00:16:48,320
And yet you married a Human.

130
00:16:48,420 --> 00:16:50,520
As ambassador to Earth it is my duty to
observe

131
00:16:50,555 --> 00:16:53,420
and understand Human behavior.

132
00:16:54,020 --> 00:16:58,320
Marrying your mother was... logical.

133
00:17:00,620 --> 00:17:02,385
Spock.

134
00:17:02,420 --> 00:17:06,320
You are fully capable of deciding
your own destiny.

135
00:17:07,320 --> 00:17:12,820
The question you face is:
Which path will you choose?

136
00:17:13,420 --> 00:17:16,420
This is something only you can decide.

137
00:17:21,820 --> 00:17:24,720
Spock. Come here, let me see you.

138
00:17:26,620 --> 00:17:29,220
- No.
- Spock.

139
00:17:37,020 --> 00:17:41,220
There's no need to be anxious.
You'll do fine.

140
00:17:41,320 --> 00:17:43,520
I am hardly anxious, mother.

141
00:17:43,720 --> 00:17:46,920
And fine has variable definitions,
fine is unacceptable.
- OK.

142
00:17:57,320 --> 00:18:00,720
- May I ask a personal query?
- Anything.

143
00:18:03,220 --> 00:18:06,320
Should I choose to complete the Vulcan
discipline of Kolinahr.

144
00:18:07,420 --> 00:18:11,120
and purge all emotion?

145
00:18:11,220 --> 00:18:15,120
I trust you will not feel it reflects
judgment upon you.

146
00:18:17,620 --> 00:18:20,120
Oh Spock.

147
00:18:21,320 --> 00:18:27,920
As always, whatever you choose to be,
you will have a proud mother.

148
00:18:32,920 --> 00:18:36,320
You have surpassed the expectations of
your instructors.

149
00:18:36,820 --> 00:18:40,820
Your final record is flawless.
With one exception.

150
00:18:40,920 --> 00:18:44,220
I see that you have applied to
Starfleet as well.

151
00:18:44,820 --> 00:18:47,485
It was logical to cultivate multiple options.

152
00:18:47,520 --> 00:18:52,220
Logical, but unnecessary. You are hereby
accepted to the Vulcan Science Academy.

153
00:18:52,520 --> 00:18:55,820
It is truly remarkable Spock that you have
achieved so much

154
00:18:55,855 --> 00:18:58,120
despite your disadvantage.

155
00:18:58,220 --> 00:19:00,820
All rise.

156
00:19:03,220 --> 00:19:08,420
If you would clarify, minister? To what
disadvantage are you referring?

157
00:19:08,920 --> 00:19:11,120
Your Human mother.

158
00:19:15,420 --> 00:19:18,320
Council, ministers, I must decline.

159
00:19:18,420 --> 00:19:21,020
No Vulcan has ever declined
admission to this Academy.

160
00:19:21,120 --> 00:19:24,370
But as I am half-human, your
record remains untarnished.

161
00:19:24,405 --> 00:19:27,620
Spock, you have made a commitment
to honor the Vulcan way.

162
00:19:27,720 --> 00:19:29,820
Why did you come before this
council today?

163
00:19:29,920 --> 00:19:32,720
Was it to satisfy your emotional need
to rebel?

164
00:19:32,820 --> 00:19:35,520
The only emotion I wish to convey
is gratitude.

165
00:19:36,820 --> 00:19:40,920
Thank you, ministers,
for your consideration.

166
00:19:42,420 --> 00:19:44,620
Live long and prosper.

167
00:20:07,820 --> 00:20:08,720
- Hi.
- Hey there.

168
00:20:13,320 --> 00:20:17,920
Hi. I'd like a Clabmin fire tea...
3 Budweiser Classics,

169
00:20:18,020 --> 00:20:21,320
2 Cardassian sunrises and...

170
00:20:21,520 --> 00:20:23,920
- Try the Slusho, it's good.
- A Slusho mix, thank you.

171
00:20:24,420 --> 00:20:26,820
That's a lot of drinks for a woman.

172
00:20:28,520 --> 00:20:31,120
- And a shot of Jack, straight up.
- Make that two. Her shot's on me.

173
00:20:31,220 --> 00:20:33,620
Her shot's on her.
Thanks, but no thanks.

174
00:20:33,720 --> 00:20:36,820
Don't you at least wanna know my name
before you completely reject me?

175
00:20:36,855 --> 00:20:38,220
I'm fine without it.

176
00:20:38,420 --> 00:20:41,620
You are fine without it. It's Jim, Jim Kirk.

177
00:20:44,120 --> 00:20:47,120
If you don't tell me your name,
I'm gonna have to make one up.

178
00:20:48,020 --> 00:20:50,320
- It's Uhura.
- Uhura? No way.

179
00:20:50,420 --> 00:20:52,620
That's the name I was gonna make
up for you.

180
00:20:52,655 --> 00:20:55,320
- Uhura what?
- Just Uhura.

181
00:20:55,420 --> 00:20:58,420
- They don't have last names in your world?
- Uhura is my last name.

182
00:20:58,520 --> 00:21:01,320
Well then don't have... first names in your world?

183
00:21:04,620 --> 00:21:07,620
- Excuse me buddy. - So, you're a cadet,
your studying. What's your focus?

184
00:21:07,720 --> 00:21:10,220
Xenolinguistics.
You have no idea what that means.

185
00:21:10,320 --> 00:21:14,720
The study of alien languages.
Morphology, phonology, syntax.

186
00:21:15,620 --> 00:21:17,620
Means you've got a talented tongue.

187
00:21:18,820 --> 00:21:20,485
I'm impressed.

188
00:21:20,520 --> 00:21:22,520
For a moment there, I thought you were just
a dumb hick

189
00:21:22,620 --> 00:21:24,620
who only has sex with farm animals.

190
00:21:24,655 --> 00:21:27,520
Well, not only.

191
00:21:28,820 --> 00:21:30,620
This townie isn't bothering you, right?

192
00:21:30,720 --> 00:21:33,620
Oh, beyond belief.
But it's nothing I can't handle.

193
00:21:33,655 --> 00:21:35,720
You could handled me.
That's an invitation.

194
00:21:36,620 --> 00:21:40,220
- Hey. You better mind your manners.
- Oh relax cupcake, it was a joke.

195
00:21:40,320 --> 00:21:43,020
Hey farm boy, maybe you can't count.

196
00:21:43,120 --> 00:21:44,985
There are 4 of us and 1 of you.

197
00:21:45,020 --> 00:21:48,320
So get some more guys and then it'll
be an even fight.

198
00:21:51,920 --> 00:21:53,720
Guys. Stop it.

199
00:21:55,920 --> 00:21:57,520
Stop it!

200
00:22:18,920 --> 00:22:20,120
Enough!

201
00:22:27,720 --> 00:22:29,420
Guys, he's had enough.

202
00:22:34,220 --> 00:22:36,720
Outside. All of you.

203
00:22:37,320 --> 00:22:39,120
- Now.
- Yes, sir.

204
00:22:39,220 --> 00:22:41,320
- What...
- I just bought a drink.

205
00:22:44,220 --> 00:22:48,220
- You all right, son?
- You can whistle really loud, you know that?

206
00:22:49,420 --> 00:22:52,220
You know I couldn't believe it when the
bartender told me who you are.

207
00:22:52,320 --> 00:22:55,220
- Who the hell am I, Captain Pike?
- Your father's son.

208
00:22:58,620 --> 00:23:00,420
Can I get another one?

209
00:23:00,520 --> 00:23:02,985
For my dissertation I was assigned the USS Kelvin.

210
00:23:03,020 --> 00:23:06,720
Something I admired about your dad, he didn't
believe in no-win scenarios.

211
00:23:07,520 --> 00:23:10,720
- Sure learned his lesson.
- Well that depends on how you define winning.

212
00:23:10,755 --> 00:23:12,520
You're here, aren't you?
- Thanks.

213
00:23:13,120 --> 00:23:16,120
You know that instinct to leap without looking,
that was his nature too

214
00:23:16,220 --> 00:23:18,420
and in my opinion it's something Starfleet's lost.

215
00:23:18,455 --> 00:23:20,420
Why are you talking to me man?

216
00:23:20,520 --> 00:23:23,420
Because I looked up your file while
you were drooling on the floor.

217
00:23:24,420 --> 00:23:27,120
Your aptitude tests are off the charts, so
what is it?

218
00:23:28,220 --> 00:23:31,120
You like being the only genius level
repeat-offender in the midwest?

219
00:23:31,155 --> 00:23:32,620
Maybe I love it.

220
00:23:32,720 --> 00:23:35,820
So your dad dies, you can saddle for
less than an ordinary life.

221
00:23:36,520 --> 00:23:41,320
Or do you feel that you were meant for
something better? Something special?

222
00:23:44,220 --> 00:23:46,520
- Enlist in Starfleet.
- Enlist?

223
00:23:48,520 --> 00:23:50,720
You guys must be way down on your
recruiting quota for the month.

224
00:23:50,755 --> 00:23:52,620
If you're half the man your father was
Jim,

225
00:23:52,720 --> 00:23:54,620
Starfleet could use you.

226
00:23:55,320 --> 00:23:58,520
You can be an officer in 4 years,
you can have your own ship in 8.

227
00:24:00,620 --> 00:24:03,720
You understand what the Federation is,
don't you? It's important,

228
00:24:03,755 --> 00:24:05,620
It's a peacekeeping and humanitarian
armada.

229
00:24:05,720 --> 00:24:07,920
We done?

230
00:24:07,955 --> 00:24:10,120
I'm done.

231
00:24:13,720 --> 00:24:17,420
Riverside shipyard. Shuttle for new
recruits leaves tomorrow - 0800.

232
00:24:21,720 --> 00:24:24,920
Your father was captain of a starship
for 12 minutes.

233
00:24:26,020 --> 00:24:30,720
He saved 800 lives, including your
mother's and yours.

234
00:24:31,920 --> 00:24:34,520
I dare you to do better.

235
00:25:59,120 --> 00:26:00,620
Nice ride man.

236
00:26:04,020 --> 00:26:05,920
It's yours.

237
00:26:06,220 --> 00:26:09,320
4 years? I'll do it in 3.

238
00:26:24,620 --> 00:26:27,220
At ease gentlemen.

239
00:26:44,820 --> 00:26:47,320
Never did get that first name.

240
00:26:47,820 --> 00:26:49,085
- You need a doctor.
- I told you people,

241
00:26:49,120 --> 00:26:51,120
I don't need a doctor,
damn it. I am a doctor.

242
00:26:51,220 --> 00:26:53,720
- You need to get back to your seat.
- I had one, in the bathroom with no windows.

243
00:26:53,755 --> 00:26:57,020
I suffer from aviofobia. That means fear
of dying in something that flies.

244
00:26:57,120 --> 00:26:59,920
Sir, for your own safety, sit down or
else I'll make you sit down!

245
00:27:03,120 --> 00:27:05,820
- Fine.
- Thank you.

246
00:27:06,120 --> 00:27:08,120
This is Captain Pike, we've been cleared
for takeoff.

247
00:27:09,420 --> 00:27:11,720
I may throw up on you.

248
00:27:11,820 --> 00:27:15,120
- I think these things are pretty safe.
- Don't pander to me kid.

249
00:27:15,220 --> 00:27:18,620
One tiny crack in the hull and our blood
boils in 13 seconds.

250
00:27:18,720 --> 00:27:21,220
A solar flare might crop up,
cook us in our seats.

251
00:27:21,720 --> 00:27:24,520
And while youâre sitting pretty with a case
of Andorian shingles,

252
00:27:24,620 --> 00:27:27,620
see if you're still so relaxed when your
eyeballs are bleeding.

253
00:27:28,020 --> 00:27:31,820
Space is disease and danger, wrapped
in darkness and silence.

254
00:27:31,920 --> 00:27:35,320
Well I hate to break this to you, but
Starfleet operates in space.

255
00:27:36,020 --> 00:27:40,520
Yeah, well... I've got nowhere else to go, the ex
wife took the whole damn planet in the divorce.

256
00:27:41,220 --> 00:27:43,520
All I've got left is my bones.

257
00:27:48,720 --> 00:27:53,020
- Jim Kirk.
- McCoy. Leonard McCoy.

258
00:28:12,320 --> 00:28:15,920
Three years later.

259
00:28:40,020 --> 00:28:43,320
Captain Nero. You've been
requested on the bridge, sir.

260
00:28:43,355 --> 00:28:45,920
Ayel says it's time.

261
00:28:50,620 --> 00:28:53,720
Sir, we've arrived at the
coordinates we calculated.

262
00:28:54,320 --> 00:28:57,220
There's nothing here. What
are your orders?

263
00:28:57,320 --> 00:28:58,885
We wait.

264
00:28:58,920 --> 00:29:02,120
We wait for the one who allowed
our home to be destroyed.

265
00:29:03,020 --> 00:29:05,420
As we've been doing for 25 years.

266
00:29:06,520 --> 00:29:09,120
- And once we've killed him?
- Kill him?

267
00:29:09,520 --> 00:29:13,320
I'm not gonna kill him.
I gonna make him watch.

268
00:29:27,520 --> 00:29:29,320
Capture that ship.

269
00:29:30,420 --> 00:29:32,720
Welcome back, Spock.

270
00:29:36,520 --> 00:29:38,920
- Why are you so happy?
- I do not know what you're talking about.

271
00:29:38,955 --> 00:29:41,320
- No, I don't suppose you do.
- Hello ladies.

272
00:29:42,220 --> 00:29:44,020
- I'm taking the test again.
- You've got to be kidding.

273
00:29:44,055 --> 00:29:45,920
Yeah, tomorrow morning.
And I want you there.

274
00:29:46,020 --> 00:29:49,220
You know I've got better things to do than
watch you embarrass yourself for the 3rd time.

275
00:29:49,320 --> 00:29:50,685
I am a doctor, Jim. I'm busy.

276
00:29:50,720 --> 00:29:53,020
Bones, it doesn't bother you that no oneâs
ever passed the test.

277
00:29:53,120 --> 00:29:55,770
Jim, it's Kobayashi Maru.
No one passes the test.

278
00:29:55,805 --> 00:29:58,420
And no one goes back for seconds,
let alone thirds.

279
00:29:59,120 --> 00:30:00,820
I've gotta study.

280
00:30:01,420 --> 00:30:03,120
Study, my ass.

281
00:30:06,220 --> 00:30:08,720
Jim, I think I love you.

282
00:30:09,820 --> 00:30:12,120
- That is so weird.
- Lights.

283
00:30:13,820 --> 00:30:16,220
- Did you just say that is so weird.
- Yeah, I did, but I...

284
00:30:16,255 --> 00:30:18,020
You don't love me too?

285
00:30:18,120 --> 00:30:20,420
- Oh, no, my roommate.
- I thought you said she was gone for the night.

286
00:30:20,455 --> 00:30:22,320
Obviously she's not. Quick, you've got...
just get under the bed.

287
00:30:22,420 --> 00:30:25,820
- Under...? - Look, just get under
the bed. She can't see you here.

288
00:30:25,920 --> 00:30:28,720
- Why not? - Because I promised her
I'd stop bringing guys back to the dorm.

289
00:30:28,755 --> 00:30:30,820
- Well how... How many guys have you...?
- Just d... just down.

290
00:30:33,520 --> 00:30:35,620
- Hey.
- Hey. How are you?

291
00:30:35,655 --> 00:30:37,720
- Good. - Strangest thing...

292
00:30:37,820 --> 00:30:39,520
I was in the long range sensor lab.

293
00:30:39,555 --> 00:30:41,320
Yeah, I thought all night...

294
00:30:41,420 --> 00:30:45,920
I was tracking solar systems and I picked
up an emergency transmission.

295
00:30:46,020 --> 00:30:47,785
- Really?
- Yeah.

296
00:30:47,820 --> 00:30:49,820
From a Klingon prison planet.

297
00:30:49,920 --> 00:30:51,085
- No.
- Yeah.

298
00:30:51,120 --> 00:30:53,820
A Klingon armada was destroyed,
47 ships.

299
00:30:53,920 --> 00:30:56,620
So, you're not going back to the
lab tonight?

300
00:31:00,720 --> 00:31:02,520
- Gaila, who is he?
- Who's who?

301
00:31:02,620 --> 00:31:04,620
The mouth-breather hiding under
your bed.

302
00:31:05,020 --> 00:31:07,220
- You could hear me breathing?
- You.

303
00:31:07,320 --> 00:31:09,420
- Big day tomorrow.
- You're gonna fail.

304
00:31:09,520 --> 00:31:11,085
- Gail, see you around.
- Get out.

305
00:31:11,120 --> 00:31:13,520
- If I pass will you tell me your first name?
- No. Good night.

306
00:31:13,620 --> 00:31:17,420
I think the fact that you picked up
a transmission is very interest...

307
00:31:19,220 --> 00:31:22,120
We're receiving a distress signal from
the USS Kobayashi Maru.

308
00:31:22,220 --> 00:31:24,385
The ship has lost power and is
stranded.

309
00:31:24,420 --> 00:31:26,420
Starfleet command has ordered
us to rescue them.

310
00:31:26,520 --> 00:31:31,520
Starfleet command has ordered
us to rescue them... Captain.

311
00:31:32,920 --> 00:31:35,920
Two Klingon vessels have entered the neutral
zone and are locking weapons on us.

312
00:31:36,620 --> 00:31:38,920
- That's OK.
- That's OK?

313
00:31:39,020 --> 00:31:40,685
Yeah, don't worry about it.

314
00:31:40,720 --> 00:31:45,020
- Did he say don't worry about it?
- Is he not taking the simulation seriously?

315
00:31:45,120 --> 00:31:47,920
Three more Klingon war birds decloaking
and targeting our ship.

316
00:31:48,020 --> 00:31:50,820
- I don't suppose this is a problem either?
- They're firing, Captain.

317
00:31:51,220 --> 00:31:53,020
Alert medical bay to prepare to receive

318
00:31:53,055 --> 00:31:54,820
all crew members from the damaged ship

319
00:31:55,320 --> 00:31:59,720
And how do you expect us to rescue them
when we're surrounded by Klingons, Captain?

320
00:31:59,820 --> 00:32:02,120
Alert medical.

321
00:32:03,720 --> 00:32:07,120
- Our ship is being hit. Shields at 60%.
- I understand.

322
00:32:07,220 --> 00:32:09,720
Should we, I don't know, fire back?

323
00:32:10,120 --> 00:32:12,520
- No.
- Of course not.

324
00:32:19,520 --> 00:32:21,320
What is this? What's going on?

325
00:32:25,420 --> 00:32:27,520
Hm. Arm photons. Prepare to fire
on the Klingon war birds.

326
00:32:27,620 --> 00:32:29,820
- Yes, sir.
- Jim, their shields are still up.

327
00:32:29,855 --> 00:32:31,120
Are they?

328
00:32:33,020 --> 00:32:36,720
- No, they're not.
- Fire on all enemy ships.

329
00:32:36,820 --> 00:32:39,320
One photon each should do
let's not waste ammunition.

330
00:32:39,420 --> 00:32:41,520
Target locked an acquired on all war birds.

331
00:32:41,820 --> 00:32:43,220
Firing.

332
00:32:47,520 --> 00:32:48,785
All ships destroyed, Captain.

333
00:32:48,820 --> 00:32:50,085
Begin rescue of the stranded crew.

334
00:32:50,120 --> 00:32:53,320
So, we've managed to eliminate all
enemy ships,

335
00:32:53,420 --> 00:32:55,320
no one on board was injured,

336
00:32:55,420 --> 00:33:00,920
and the successful rescue of the
Kobayashi Maru crew is under way.

337
00:33:05,220 --> 00:33:07,920
How the hell did that kid beat your test?

338
00:33:10,720 --> 00:33:13,120
I do not know.

339
00:33:13,520 --> 00:33:16,420
This session has been called to resolve a
troubling matter.

340
00:33:17,020 --> 00:33:19,120
James T. Kirk, step forward.

341
00:33:21,020 --> 00:33:23,720
Cadet Kirk, evidence has been submitted
to this council,

342
00:33:23,820 --> 00:33:26,720
suggesting that you violated the
ethical code of conduct

343
00:33:26,755 --> 00:33:30,120
pursuing to regulation 17.43
of the Starfleet code.

344
00:33:31,220 --> 00:33:33,520
Is there anything you care to say
before we begin, sir?

345
00:33:35,320 --> 00:33:39,120
Yes. I believe I have the right
to face my accuser directly?

346
00:33:43,320 --> 00:33:44,620
Step forward please.

347
00:33:45,620 --> 00:33:49,420
This is Commander Spock. He is one
of our most distinguished graduates.

348
00:33:49,820 --> 00:33:53,320
He's programmed the Kobayashi Maru
exam for the last 4 years.

349
00:33:55,520 --> 00:33:56,620
Commander.

350
00:33:57,320 --> 00:34:00,220
Cadet Kirk, you somehow managed to install
and activate a subroutine

351
00:34:00,320 --> 00:34:03,120
in the programming code, thereby changing the
conditions of the test.

352
00:34:04,720 --> 00:34:07,820
- Your point being?
- In academic vernacular - you cheated.

353
00:34:09,920 --> 00:34:13,720
Let me ask you something I think we all
know the answer to.

354
00:34:14,520 --> 00:34:18,520
The test itself is a cheat, isn't it?
You programmed it to be unwinnable.

355
00:34:18,920 --> 00:34:21,520
Your argument precludes the ability
of a no-win scenario?

356
00:34:21,620 --> 00:34:23,785
I don't believe in no-win scenarios.

357
00:34:23,820 --> 00:34:27,320
Then not only did you violate the rules, you
also failed to understand the principle lesson.

358
00:34:27,420 --> 00:34:28,820
Please, enlighten me.

359
00:34:28,920 --> 00:34:33,220
You of all people should know, cadet
Kirk, a captain cannot cheat death.

360
00:34:36,220 --> 00:34:38,920
- I of all people?
- Your father,

361
00:34:39,120 --> 00:34:42,820
Lt. George Kirk assumed command of his vessel
before being killed in action, did he not?

362
00:34:42,920 --> 00:34:47,220
- I don't think you like the fact that I beat your test.
- Further more you have failed to define the purpose of the test

363
00:34:47,320 --> 00:34:50,220
- Enlighten me again.
- The purpose to experience fear.

364
00:34:51,520 --> 00:34:54,920
Fear in the face of certain death.
To accept that fear

365
00:34:55,020 --> 00:34:57,520
and maintain control of oneself
and one's crew.

366
00:34:58,020 --> 00:35:00,920
This is a quality expected in
every Starfleet captain.

367
00:35:04,220 --> 00:35:05,420
Excuse me, sir.

368
00:35:11,920 --> 00:35:14,220
We've received a distress
call from Vulcan.

369
00:35:14,620 --> 00:35:17,520
With our primary fleet engaged
in the Laurentian system,

370
00:35:17,620 --> 00:35:21,120
I hereby order all cadets to report
to hangar 1 immediately.

371
00:35:21,220 --> 00:35:22,220
Dismissed.

372
00:35:28,720 --> 00:35:31,420
- Who was that pointy-eared bastard?
- I do not know.

373
00:35:31,520 --> 00:35:33,420
But I like him.

374
00:35:38,820 --> 00:35:40,320
Bracer, USS Farragut.

375
00:35:40,420 --> 00:35:43,720
McCoy, USS Enterprise.
McGrath, USS Walcott.

376
00:35:43,820 --> 00:35:45,220
Spader, USS Hood.

377
00:35:45,320 --> 00:35:47,020
Welcome to Starfleet.
Godspeed.

378
00:35:49,520 --> 00:35:51,520
He didn't call my name.

379
00:35:52,220 --> 00:35:56,720
Commander, sir, you didn't call
my name, Kirk, James T.

380
00:35:57,020 --> 00:35:59,920
Kirk, you're on academic suspension,
that means you're grounded

381
00:36:00,420 --> 00:36:02,120
until the academy board rules.

382
00:36:05,220 --> 00:36:07,720
Jim, the board will rule in your favor.

383
00:36:08,120 --> 00:36:09,720
Most likely.

384
00:36:11,320 --> 00:36:13,720
Look Jim, I've gotta go.

385
00:36:14,320 --> 00:36:16,820
Yeah. Yeah, go. Be safe.

386
00:36:24,620 --> 00:36:26,820
- Excuse me.
- Yeah. Yeah. Sorry.

387
00:36:31,620 --> 00:36:33,020
Damn it.

388
00:36:35,320 --> 00:36:36,985
Come with me.

389
00:36:37,020 --> 00:36:40,520
Uhura, USS Farragut.
Petrovsky, USS Antares.

390
00:36:40,620 --> 00:36:42,620
Go to your stations and good luck.

391
00:36:46,220 --> 00:36:49,320
- Bones, where are we going?
- You'll see.

392
00:36:51,120 --> 00:36:52,685
- Commander, a word?
- Yes, lieutenant?

393
00:36:52,720 --> 00:36:55,020
- Was I not one of your top students?
- Indeed you were.

394
00:36:55,120 --> 00:36:59,220
And did I not on multiple occasions
demonstrate an exceptional oral sensitivity

395
00:36:59,320 --> 00:37:02,920
and I quote "an unparalleled ability
to identify sonic anomalies

396
00:37:03,020 --> 00:37:04,820
in subspace transmission tests"?

397
00:37:04,855 --> 00:37:06,320
Consistently, yes.

398
00:37:06,420 --> 00:37:09,820
And while you were well aware that I'm qualified
and desire to serve on the USS Enterprise,

399
00:37:09,855 --> 00:37:11,820
I'm assigned to the Farragut?

400
00:37:11,920 --> 00:37:15,020
It was an attempt to avoid
the appearance of favoritism.

401
00:37:15,120 --> 00:37:17,220
No. I'm assigned to the Enterprise.

402
00:37:21,420 --> 00:37:23,420
- Yes, I believe you are.
- Thank you.

403
00:37:24,720 --> 00:37:26,920
- What are you doing?
- I'm doing you a favor.

404
00:37:27,020 --> 00:37:29,920
I couldnât just leave you there
looking all pathetic. Take a seat.

405
00:37:30,020 --> 00:37:31,820
Let me give you a vaccine
against viral infection

406
00:37:31,920 --> 00:37:33,520
from the Lovaran mud fleas.

407
00:37:35,220 --> 00:37:37,120
- What for?
- To give you the symptoms.

408
00:37:37,420 --> 00:37:40,320
- What are you talking about? - You're
gonna start to lose vision in your left eye.

409
00:37:40,420 --> 00:37:41,785
Yeah, I already have.

410
00:37:41,820 --> 00:37:44,420
Oh, and you're gonna get a really bad
headache and flop sweat.

411
00:37:44,820 --> 00:37:47,420
- You call this a favor?
- Yeah, you owe me one.

412
00:37:49,320 --> 00:37:53,820
Kirk, James T. He is not cleared
for duty aboard the Enterprise.

413
00:37:54,020 --> 00:37:56,820
Medical code states the treatment and
transport of a patient is to be determined

414
00:37:56,920 --> 00:37:59,720
at the discretion of his attending physician.

415
00:37:59,820 --> 00:38:02,585
Which is me. So I'm taking Mr. Kirk aboard.

416
00:38:02,620 --> 00:38:05,120
Or you would you like to explain to
Captain Pike

417
00:38:05,220 --> 00:38:09,320
why Enterprise warped into a crisis
without one of its senior medical officers?

418
00:38:10,420 --> 00:38:12,820
- As you were.
- As you were. Come on.

419
00:38:31,420 --> 00:38:32,620
I might throw up on you.

420
00:38:33,320 --> 00:38:35,420
Jim, you've gotta look at this.

421
00:38:35,920 --> 00:38:38,020
- Jim, look.
- What?

422
00:39:35,020 --> 00:39:36,920
We need to get you changed.

423
00:39:37,220 --> 00:39:39,120
I don't feel right. I feel like I'm leaking.

424
00:39:39,155 --> 00:39:41,220
Damn, it's that pointy-eared bastard.

425
00:39:59,020 --> 00:40:01,320
- Mr. Spock.
- Captain.

426
00:40:01,820 --> 00:40:04,720
- Engineering reports ready for launch.
- Thank you.

427
00:40:04,820 --> 00:40:07,420
Ladies and gentlemen, the maiden
voyage of our newest flagship

428
00:40:07,455 --> 00:40:10,020
deserves more pomp than circumstance
we can afford today.

429
00:40:10,820 --> 00:40:13,420
The christening will just have to
be our reward for a safe return.

430
00:40:14,120 --> 00:40:15,220
Carry on.

431
00:40:15,620 --> 00:40:17,920
All decks, this is Captain Pike.
Prepare for immediate departure.

432
00:40:18,020 --> 00:40:19,285
Helm, thrusters.

433
00:40:19,320 --> 00:40:21,720
Morrings retracted, Captain, dock
control reports ready.

434
00:40:21,920 --> 00:40:24,420
Thrusters fired.
Separating from space dock.

435
00:40:33,920 --> 00:40:36,720
The fleet's cleared space dock, Captain.
All ships ready for warp.

436
00:40:37,220 --> 00:40:39,320
- Set course for Vulcan.
- Aye-aye, Captain.

437
00:40:40,420 --> 00:40:41,920
Course laid in.

438
00:40:42,620 --> 00:40:44,820
Maximum warp. Punch it.

439
00:41:02,020 --> 00:41:05,020
- Lieutenant, where's helmsmen McKenna?
- He has lung worms sir.

440
00:41:05,055 --> 00:41:06,920
He couldn't report to his post.

441
00:41:07,020 --> 00:41:10,120
- I'm Hikaru Sulu.
- And you are a pilot, right?

442
00:41:10,720 --> 00:41:15,120
Very much so, sir. I'm a...
I'm not sure what's wrong here.

443
00:41:15,220 --> 00:41:17,020
Is the parking brake on?

444
00:41:17,520 --> 00:41:18,585
No.

445
00:41:18,620 --> 00:41:19,585
I'll figure it out, I'm just...

446
00:41:19,620 --> 00:41:21,820
Have you disengaged the external
inertial dampener?

447
00:41:26,920 --> 00:41:29,220
- Ready for warp, sir.
- Let's punch it.

448
00:41:36,520 --> 00:41:38,220
- Where are we?
- Medical bay.

449
00:41:38,320 --> 00:41:40,320
- This isn't worth it.
- A little suffering's good for the soul.

450
00:41:40,355 --> 00:41:41,320
Hi, how are you?

451
00:41:42,120 --> 00:41:45,620
- My mouth is itchy. Is that normal?
- Well, those symptoms won't last long.

452
00:41:45,720 --> 00:41:48,820
- I'm going to give you a mild sedative.
- Oh, I wish I didn't know you.

453
00:41:48,855 --> 00:41:49,720
Don't be such an infant.

454
00:41:52,120 --> 00:41:53,720
How long is it supposed to...

455
00:41:54,220 --> 00:41:55,820
Unbelievable.

456
00:41:57,120 --> 00:41:58,320
Engines at maximum warp Captain.

457
00:41:58,420 --> 00:42:00,620
Russian whiz kid, what's your name?
Chenkov? Chirpov?

458
00:42:00,820 --> 00:42:03,920
- Ensign Chekov, Pavel Andrejevic, sir.
- Fine.

459
00:42:04,020 --> 00:42:06,720
Chekov, Pavel Andrejevic,
begin ship wide mission broadcast.

460
00:42:07,020 --> 00:42:08,720
Yes, sir. Happy to.

461
00:42:09,420 --> 00:42:13,220
Ensign authorization code
95 Wictor Wictor 2.

462
00:42:13,320 --> 00:42:15,420
Authorization not recognized.

463
00:42:15,520 --> 00:42:21,820
Ensign authorization code
95 Victor Victor 2.

464
00:42:22,420 --> 00:42:24,385
Access granted.

465
00:42:24,420 --> 00:42:26,920
May I have your attention please.

466
00:42:27,520 --> 00:42:32,920
At 22:00, telemetry detected an anomaly
in the neutral zone.

467
00:42:33,020 --> 00:42:36,620
What appeared to be a lightning
storm in space.

468
00:42:36,720 --> 00:42:41,520
Soon after, Starfleet received a distress
signal from the Vulcan high command

469
00:42:41,620 --> 00:42:45,420
that their planet was experiencing
seismic activity.

470
00:42:45,520 --> 00:42:49,320
Our mission is to assess the
condition of Vulcan

471
00:42:49,420 --> 00:42:52,920
and assist in evacuations
if necessary.

472
00:42:53,420 --> 00:42:58,120
We should be arriving at Vulcan within
3 minutes. Thank you for your time.

473
00:42:59,720 --> 00:43:01,585
Lightning storm.

474
00:43:01,620 --> 00:43:04,320
Aah Jim, you're awake. How do you feel?

