an endangered species.

711
01:05:18,689 --> 01:05:20,989
I'm sorry.

712
01:05:22,389 --> 01:05:26,989
I'm so sorry.

713
01:05:41,089 --> 01:05:45,089
What do you need.
Tell me. Tell me.

714
01:05:53,689 --> 01:05:55,789
I need everyone...

715
01:05:56,889 --> 01:06:11,789
- ... to continue performing admirably.
- OK.

716
01:06:26,889 --> 01:06:28,889
You must have a lot of questions for me.

717
01:06:29,889 --> 01:06:31,989
I only have one for you.

718
01:06:33,589 --> 01:06:37,589
I need the subspace frequencies of
Starfleet's border protection grids.

719
01:06:38,089 --> 01:06:40,789
Specifically those surrounding Earth.

720
01:06:42,489 --> 01:06:45,689
Christopher, answer my question.

721
01:06:45,789 --> 01:06:48,989
No, you answer for the genocide you just
committed against a peaceful planet.

722
01:06:49,024 --> 01:06:51,689
No, I prevented genocide.

723
01:06:54,689 --> 01:06:58,889
In my time, where I come from,
this is a simple mining vessel.

724
01:06:59,689 --> 01:07:02,889
I chose a life of honest labor.

725
01:07:02,989 --> 01:07:06,289
to provide for myself and the wife
who was expecting my child.

726
01:07:06,889 --> 01:07:09,254
I was off planet doing my job

727
01:07:09,289 --> 01:07:11,389
while your Federation did nothing.

728
01:07:11,789 --> 01:07:14,789
And allowed my people to burn
while our planet broke in half.

729
01:07:15,389 --> 01:07:18,489
And Spock, he didn't help us.
He betrayed us.

730
01:07:18,589 --> 01:07:22,189
No, no... you're confused. You're misinformed.
Romulus hasn't been destroyed.

731
01:07:22,289 --> 01:07:25,789
It's out there right now. You're blaming the
Federation for something that hasn't happened...

732
01:07:25,889 --> 01:07:29,089
It has happened! I watched it happen!
I saw it happen!

733
01:07:29,189 --> 01:07:30,789
Don't tell me it didn't happen!

734
01:07:35,489 --> 01:07:39,689
And when I lost her.
I promised myself retribution.

735
01:07:40,389 --> 01:07:44,089
And for 25 years I planned my
revenge against the Federation.

736
01:07:44,589 --> 01:07:48,089
And forgot what it was like to
live a normal life.

737
01:07:48,189 --> 01:07:50,189
I did not forget the pain.

738
01:07:51,989 --> 01:07:55,489
It's a pain that every surviving
Vulcan now shares.

739
01:07:57,189 --> 01:07:59,189
My purpose, Christopher,

740
01:07:59,289 --> 01:08:03,089
is to not simply avoid the destruction
of the home that I love

741
01:08:04,689 --> 01:08:09,589
but to create a Romulus that
exists free of the Federation.

742
01:08:12,489 --> 01:08:15,689
You see only then will she be truly saved.

743
01:08:16,489 --> 01:08:20,589
That is why I will destroy all the
remaining Federation planets.

744
01:08:21,089 --> 01:08:22,889
Starting with yours.

745
01:08:23,789 --> 01:08:26,289
Then we have nothing left to discuss.

746
01:08:30,489 --> 01:08:33,389
You will give me the frequencies to
disable Earth's defenses.

747
01:08:36,689 --> 01:08:40,889
Centaurian slugs. They latch
on to your brain stem...

748
01:08:42,789 --> 01:08:45,189
and release a toxin that will
force you to answer.

749
01:08:46,889 --> 01:08:48,789
Frequencies please, sir.

750
01:08:49,589 --> 01:08:51,789
Christopher Pike, captain of
the USS Enterprise...

751
01:08:51,824 --> 01:08:52,689
As you wish.

752
01:09:00,889 --> 01:09:02,554
Have you confirmed that Nero
is heading for Earth?

753
01:09:02,589 --> 01:09:05,289
Their trajectory suggests no
other destination, Captain.

754
01:09:05,889 --> 01:09:07,089
Thank you, Lt.

755
01:09:07,389 --> 01:09:09,689
Earth may be his next stop, but
we have to assume

756
01:09:09,789 --> 01:09:11,689
every Federation planet's a target

757
01:09:11,724 --> 01:09:13,189
Out of the chair.

758
01:09:13,289 --> 01:09:17,389
Well, if the Federation is the target,
why didn't they destroy us?

759
01:09:17,489 --> 01:09:20,389
Why would they? Why waste a weapon?
We obviously weren't a threat.

760
01:09:20,489 --> 01:09:25,089
That is not it. He said he wanted me to see
something. The destruction of my home planet.

761
01:09:25,189 --> 01:09:27,054
How the hell did they do that, by the way?

762
01:09:27,089 --> 01:09:29,289
And where did the Romulans get
that kind of weaponry?

763
01:09:29,389 --> 01:09:32,989
The engineering comprehension necessary
to artificially create a black hole

764
01:09:33,089 --> 01:09:34,654
may suggest an answer.

765
01:09:34,689 --> 01:09:37,089
Such technology could theoretically
be manipulated

766
01:09:37,189 --> 01:09:38,989
to create a tunnel through space-time.

767
01:09:39,389 --> 01:09:41,189
Damn it man, I am a doctor, not physicist.

768
01:09:41,289 --> 01:09:43,454
Are you actually suggesting
they're from the future?

769
01:09:43,489 --> 01:09:46,489
If you eliminate the impossible, what ever
remains, however improbable

770
01:09:46,589 --> 01:09:47,789
must be the truth.

771
01:09:47,889 --> 01:09:48,854
How poetic.

772
01:09:48,889 --> 01:09:52,489
Then what would an angry future
Romulan want with Captain Pike?

773
01:09:52,524 --> 01:09:55,089
As captain he does know details
of Starfleet's defenses.

774
01:09:55,189 --> 01:09:56,789
What we need to do is catch
up to that ship,

775
01:09:56,889 --> 01:09:58,954
disable it, take it over and get Pike back.

776
01:09:58,989 --> 01:10:03,389
We are technologically outmatched in every
way. A rescue attempt would be illogical.

777
01:10:03,489 --> 01:10:06,289
Nero's ship would have to drop
out of warp for us to overtake it.

778
01:10:06,389 --> 01:10:09,589
Then what about assigning engineering
crews to try and boost our warp yield?

779
01:10:09,689 --> 01:10:11,889
Remaining power and crew are being
used to repair radiation leaks

780
01:10:11,989 --> 01:10:13,654
on the lower decks. The damage...

781
01:10:13,689 --> 01:10:16,089
- OK. All right. All right. - ... communications.
Without it... - There's got to be some way.

782
01:10:16,189 --> 01:10:19,289
- ... we cannot contact Starfleet. We
must gather with the rest of Starfleet.

783
01:10:19,324 --> 01:10:22,389
To balance the terms of the next engagement,
- There won't be a next engagement.

784
01:10:22,489 --> 01:10:25,189
By the time we gathered it'll be too late.

785
01:10:25,889 --> 01:10:27,989
Look, you say he's from the future and
knows what's gonna happen

786
01:10:28,024 --> 01:10:30,389
then the logical thing is to be unpredictable.

787
01:10:30,489 --> 01:10:33,289
You're assuming that Nero knows
how event's are predicted to unfold.

788
01:10:33,889 --> 01:10:36,454
The contrary. Nero's very presence
has altered the flow of history

789
01:10:36,489 --> 01:10:39,489
beginning with the attack on the USS Kelvin,
culminating with the events of today,

790
01:10:39,589 --> 01:10:44,689
thereby creating an entire new chain of incidents
that cannot be anticipated by either party.

791
01:10:44,789 --> 01:10:46,189
An alternate reality.

792
01:10:47,489 --> 01:10:49,089
Precisely.

793
01:10:49,289 --> 01:10:50,939
Whatever our lives might have been

794
01:10:50,974 --> 01:10:52,589
if the time continuum was disrupted

795
01:10:53,689 --> 01:10:55,889
our destinies have changed.

796
01:10:55,989 --> 01:10:58,489
Mr. Sulu, plot a course for the
Laurentian system. Warp factor 3.

797
01:10:58,589 --> 01:10:59,889
Spock, don't do that.

798
01:10:59,989 --> 01:11:04,389
Running back to the rest of the fleet for
a con fab is a massive waste of time...

799
01:11:04,489 --> 01:11:06,189
These orders were issued by
Captain Pike when he left.

800
01:11:06,224 --> 01:11:07,854
He also ordered us to go back and get him.

801
01:11:07,889 --> 01:11:11,289
- Spock, you are captain now. You have...
- I am aware of my responsibilities...

802
01:11:11,389 --> 01:11:13,689
Every second we waste Nero's
getting closer to his next target.

803
01:11:13,789 --> 01:11:16,789
That is correct and why I'm instructing
you to accept the fact that I'm...

804
01:11:16,889 --> 01:11:20,789
I will not allow us to go backwards...
... instead of hunting Nero down.

805
01:11:20,889 --> 01:11:23,189
Security, escort him out.

806
01:11:32,289 --> 01:11:33,689
- No.
- Jim!

807
01:11:38,889 --> 01:11:40,889
Get him off this ship.

808
01:12:00,989 --> 01:12:02,254
Computer, where am I?

809
01:12:02,289 --> 01:12:05,689
Location: Delta Vega.
Class M planet. Unsafe.

810
01:12:05,789 --> 01:12:09,589
There is a Starfleet outpost 14km
to the northwest.

811
01:12:09,689 --> 01:12:13,089
- Remain in your pod...
- Oh, you've gotta be kidding me.

812
01:12:55,789 --> 01:12:59,289
Stardate 2258.42.

813
01:13:00,089 --> 01:13:03,489
...for... for... Whatever.

814
01:13:03,889 --> 01:13:07,389
Acting Captain Spock has
marooned me on Delta Vega.

815
01:13:07,589 --> 01:13:12,189
What I believe to be a violation
of security protocol 49.09

816
01:13:12,289 --> 01:13:14,789
governing the treatment of prisoners
aboard a starship.

817
01:15:25,289 --> 01:15:27,889
James T. Kirk.

818
01:15:29,289 --> 01:15:31,389
- Excuse me?
- How did you find me?

819
01:15:33,789 --> 01:15:35,789
How do you know my name?

820
01:15:36,789 --> 01:15:40,789
I have been and always shall be your friend.

821
01:15:44,389 --> 01:15:46,989
Look, I don't know you.

822
01:15:47,024 --> 01:15:49,689
I am Spock.

823
01:15:53,889 --> 01:15:55,289
Bullshit.

824
01:15:55,389 --> 01:15:57,889
It is remarkably pleasing to see
you again old friend.

825
01:15:58,689 --> 01:16:01,189
Especially after the events of today.

826
01:16:03,289 --> 01:16:05,254
Sir, I appreciate what you did for me today

827
01:16:05,289 --> 01:16:08,989
but if you were Spock, you'd know
we're not friends at all.

828
01:16:09,089 --> 01:16:11,489
You hate me. You marooned
me here for mutiny.

829
01:16:11,589 --> 01:16:13,554
- Mutiny?
- Yes.

830
01:16:13,589 --> 01:16:15,589
You are not the captain?

831
01:16:18,689 --> 01:16:22,589
No, no... You're the captain.

832
01:16:22,889 --> 01:16:25,189
Pike was taken hostage.

833
01:16:25,589 --> 01:16:27,589
By Nero?

834
01:16:32,689 --> 01:16:35,089
What do you know about him?

835
01:16:35,589 --> 01:16:38,389
He is a particularly troubled Romulan.

836
01:16:39,589 --> 01:16:41,689
Please. Allow me.

837
01:16:42,489 --> 01:16:43,789
It will be easier.

838
01:16:44,089 --> 01:16:47,689
- Whoa, whoa. What are you doing?
- Our minds, one and together.

839
01:16:50,189 --> 01:16:56,089
129 years from now, a star will explode
and threaten to destroy the galaxy.

840
01:16:57,789 --> 01:17:00,589
That is where I'm from Jim.

841
01:17:00,689 --> 01:17:02,089
The future.

842
01:17:06,089 --> 01:17:08,489
A star went supernova.

843
01:17:10,189 --> 01:17:12,689
Consuming everything in its path.

844
01:17:12,789 --> 01:17:16,089
I promised the Romulans that I
will save their planet.

845
01:17:21,589 --> 01:17:23,889
We outfitted our fastest ship.

846
01:17:24,989 --> 01:17:27,589
Using red matter I would create a black hole

847
01:17:27,689 --> 01:17:30,389
which would absorb the exploding star.

848
01:17:31,689 --> 01:17:34,689
I was on route when the unthinkable happened.

849
01:17:36,089 --> 01:17:39,689
The supernova destroyed Romulus.

850
01:17:44,989 --> 01:17:46,889
I had little time.

851
01:17:49,189 --> 01:17:53,089
I had to extract the red matter
and shoot it into the supernova.

852
01:18:09,689 --> 01:18:12,389
As I began my return trip I was intercepted.

853
01:18:12,489 --> 01:18:16,589
- He called himself Nero,
- ... collapse of Romulan Empire.

854
01:18:16,689 --> 01:18:20,489
In my attempt to escape, both of
us were pulled into the black hole.

855
01:18:29,189 --> 01:18:32,689
Nero went through first.
He was the first to arrive.

856
01:18:40,089 --> 01:18:43,189
Nero and his crew spent the next 25 years
awaiting my arrival.

857
01:18:43,289 --> 01:18:45,389
But what was years for Nero

858
01:18:46,989 --> 01:18:49,089
was only seconds for me.

859
01:18:49,989 --> 01:18:52,289
I went through the black hole.

860
01:18:54,289 --> 01:18:57,389
Nero was waiting for me.

861
01:19:02,489 --> 01:19:05,589
He held me responsible for the
loss of his world.

862
01:19:07,489 --> 01:19:10,089
He captured my vessel and spared my life.

863
01:19:11,189 --> 01:19:16,189
For one reason. So that
I would know his pain.

864
01:19:18,289 --> 01:19:22,289
He beamed me here so that
I can observe his vengeance.

865
01:19:24,189 --> 01:19:27,189
As he was helpless to save his planet

866
01:19:27,289 --> 01:19:30,989
I would be helpless to save mine.

867
01:19:33,289 --> 01:19:37,589
Billions of lives lost because of me, Jim.

868
01:19:37,689 --> 01:19:40,589
Because I failed.

869
01:19:42,889 --> 01:19:46,989
Forgive me. Emotional transference
is an effect of the mind meld.

870
01:19:54,189 --> 01:19:57,289
- So you do feel.
- Yes.

871
01:19:57,389 --> 01:20:00,189
Going back in time you changed all our lives.

872
01:20:01,189 --> 01:20:04,089
Jim, we must go.

873
01:20:04,589 --> 01:20:06,889
There is a Starfleet outpost not far from here.

874
01:20:08,489 --> 01:20:10,089
Wait.

875
01:20:10,789 --> 01:20:12,989
Where you came from...

876
01:20:15,089 --> 01:20:16,989
...did I know my father?

877
01:20:18,089 --> 01:20:19,489
Yes.

878
01:20:19,889 --> 01:20:23,189
You often spoke of him as being
your inspiration for joining Starfleet.

879
01:20:24,289 --> 01:20:27,689
He proudly lived to see you become
captain of the Enterprise.

880
01:20:28,289 --> 01:20:29,554
Captain?

881
01:20:29,589 --> 01:20:32,489
A ship we must return you to
as soon as possible.

882
01:20:41,189 --> 01:20:43,689
- Warp 3, sir.
- Course 151-3.

883
01:20:43,789 --> 01:20:45,989
- Laurentian system, sir.
- Thank you gentlemen.

884
01:20:46,489 --> 01:20:49,989
- You wanted to see me?
- Yes. Doctor.

885
01:20:51,289 --> 01:20:53,489
I am aware that James Kirk is a friend of yours.

886
01:20:53,589 --> 01:20:56,489
I recognize that supporting me
as you did must have been difficult.

887
01:20:56,524 --> 01:20:58,089
Is that a thank you?

888
01:20:58,489 --> 01:21:02,989
- I am simply acknowledging your difficulties.
- Permission to speak freely, sir.

889
01:21:04,389 --> 01:21:06,189
- I welcome it.
- Do you?

890
01:21:07,089 --> 01:21:09,989
Ok then. Are you out of your Vulcan mind?

891
01:21:10,689 --> 01:21:14,889
Are you making a logical choice sending
Kirk away? Probably. But the right one?

892
01:21:15,089 --> 01:21:18,089
Back home we've got a saying. If you're
gonna ride in the Kentucky derby

893
01:21:18,189 --> 01:21:20,354
you don't leave your prized stallion in the stable

894
01:21:20,389 --> 01:21:24,089
A curious metaphor, Doctor,
as a stallion it must first be broken

895
01:21:24,189 --> 01:21:25,989
before it can reach its potential.

896
01:21:26,689 --> 01:21:28,889
My God man. You could at least
act like it was a hard decision.

897
01:21:28,989 --> 01:21:32,389
I intend to insist in the effort to reestablish
communication with Starfleet.

898
01:21:32,789 --> 01:21:36,589
However, if crew moral is better served
by my roaming the halls weeping

899
01:21:36,689 --> 01:21:39,789
I would gladly defer to your medical expertise.

900
01:21:41,189 --> 01:21:42,689
Excuse me.

901
01:21:46,889 --> 01:21:48,889
Green blooded hobgoblin.

902
01:23:09,589 --> 01:23:11,089
What?

903
01:23:14,789 --> 01:23:16,889
You realize how unacceptable this is?

904
01:23:16,989 --> 01:23:18,254
- Fascinating.
- What?

905
01:23:18,289 --> 01:23:21,454
I am sure you're just doing your job, but
could you not come a wee bit sooner?

906
01:23:21,489 --> 01:23:26,189
Six months I've been here. Living off Starfleet
botty nips and a promise of a good meal.

907
01:23:26,389 --> 01:23:28,854
And I know exactly what's going on here.

908
01:23:28,889 --> 01:23:32,989
Ok? Punishment, isn't it? Ongoing. For
something that was clearly an accident.

909
01:23:33,089 --> 01:23:35,989
- You are Montgomery Scott.
- You know him?

910
01:23:36,089 --> 01:23:37,789
Yeah, it's me. You're in the right place.

911
01:23:38,089 --> 01:23:41,089
Unless thereâs another hard working
equally starved Starfleet officer around.

912
01:23:41,189 --> 01:23:43,389
- Me.
- Get it, shut up.

913
01:23:44,189 --> 01:23:47,289
You aren't doing anything. You can
eat, like, a bean and you're done.

914
01:23:47,689 --> 01:23:49,789
I'm talking about food, real food.

915
01:23:49,889 --> 01:23:52,489
But you're here now. So, thank you.
Where is it?

916
01:23:52,589 --> 01:23:56,589
You are in fact a Mr. Scott who postulated
the theory of transwarp beaming?

917
01:23:56,689 --> 01:23:59,789
That's what I'm talking about.
How'd ya think I wound up here?

918
01:24:00,189 --> 01:24:01,889
I had a little debate with my instructor

919
01:24:02,089 --> 01:24:05,589
on the issue of relativistic physics and
how it pertains to subspace travel.

920
01:24:05,689 --> 01:24:09,689
He seemed to think that the range of
transporting something like a grapefruit

921
01:24:09,789 --> 01:24:11,654
was limited to about a 100 miles.

922
01:24:11,689 --> 01:24:15,389
I told him that I could not only beam a
grapefruit from one planet to the adjacent planet

923
01:24:15,489 --> 01:24:18,089
in the same system, which is easy by the way

924
01:24:18,189 --> 01:24:19,989
I could do it with a life form.

925
01:24:20,689 --> 01:24:23,089
So, I tested it on admiral Archer's prize beagle.

926
01:24:23,124 --> 01:24:24,689
I know that dog. What happened to it?

927
01:24:25,189 --> 01:24:28,489
I'll tell you when it reappears. I don't
know. I do feel guilty about that.

928
01:24:28,589 --> 01:24:31,489
What if I told you that your transwarp theory was correct?

929
01:24:31,589 --> 01:24:34,789
That it is indeed possible to beam onto
a ship that is travelling at warp speed?

930
01:24:34,889 --> 01:24:37,389
I think that if that equation had been
discovered I'd have heard about it.

931
01:24:37,489 --> 01:24:39,489
The reason you haven't
heard of it, Mr. Scott,

932
01:24:39,524 --> 01:24:41,789
is because you haven't discovered it yet.

933
01:24:47,289 --> 01:24:51,089
- Are you from the future?
- He is. I'm not.

934
01:24:51,189 --> 01:24:53,889
Well that's brilliant. Do they still
have sandwiches there?

935
01:24:54,889 --> 01:24:56,989
Well, she's a wee bit dodgy.

936
01:24:57,389 --> 01:24:59,789
Shield emitters are totally bum jacked
as well as a few other things.

937
01:24:59,889 --> 01:25:01,289
In you go.

938
01:25:02,189 --> 01:25:04,289
So, the Enterprise has had it's
maiden voyage, has it?

939
01:25:04,324 --> 01:25:05,989
She is one well endowed lady.

940
01:25:06,089 --> 01:25:10,089
I'd like to get my hands on her ample nacelles,
if you'd pardon the engineering parlance.

941
01:25:12,389 --> 01:25:16,289
Except, the thing is, even if I believed you.
Where you're from, what I've done...

942
01:25:16,389 --> 01:25:20,689
Which I don't, by the way. We're still
talking about beaming aboard the Enterprise

943
01:25:20,789 --> 01:25:23,589
while she's travelling faster than light
without a proper receiving pad.

944
01:25:23,689 --> 01:25:26,189
Get off there. It's not a climbing frame.

945
01:25:26,789 --> 01:25:28,054
The notion of transwarp beaming

946
01:25:28,089 --> 01:25:31,389
is like trying to hit a bullet with a smaller bullet

947
01:25:31,489 --> 01:25:34,389
whilst wearing a blindfold, riding a horse.

948
01:25:34,489 --> 01:25:35,454
What's that?

949
01:25:35,489 --> 01:25:38,689
Your equation for achieving transwarp beaming.

950
01:25:41,089 --> 01:25:42,889
You're out of it...

951
01:25:46,289 --> 01:25:50,189
Imagine that. It never occurred to me to
think of space as the thing that was moving

952
01:25:50,889 --> 01:25:52,889
You're coming with us, right?

953
01:25:54,789 --> 01:25:56,989
No, Jim. That is not my destiny.

954
01:25:57,789 --> 01:25:59,389
Your dest...

955
01:26:00,089 --> 01:26:02,589
He... The other Spock is not gonna believe me.
Only you can explain what the hell has happened.

956
01:26:02,624 --> 01:26:06,689
Under no circumstances can he be made aware
of my existence. You must promise me this.

957
01:26:06,789 --> 01:26:11,089
So you're telling me I can't tell you that I'm following
you're own orders. Why not? What happens?

958
01:26:11,289 --> 01:26:13,589
Jim, this is one rule you cannot break.

959
01:26:13,689 --> 01:26:17,289
To stop Nero, you alone must
take command of your ship.

960
01:26:17,389 --> 01:26:19,189
How? Over your dead body?

961
01:26:19,224 --> 01:26:20,254
Preferably, not.

962
01:26:20,289 --> 01:26:23,189
However, there is Starfleet regulation 619.

963
01:26:23,489 --> 01:26:29,289
619 states that any command officer who is
emotionally compromised by the mission at hand

964
01:26:29,489 --> 01:26:32,089
must resign said command.

965
01:26:34,389 --> 01:26:38,189
So, you're saying that I have to
emotionally compromise you... guys?

966
01:26:38,289 --> 01:26:41,489
Jim, I just lost my planet.

967
01:26:42,589 --> 01:26:46,189
I can tell you, I am emotionally compromised.

968
01:26:46,589 --> 01:26:49,289
What you must do is get me to show it.

969
01:26:49,389 --> 01:26:52,089
Aye then laddie. Live or die.
Let's get this over with.

970
01:26:58,889 --> 01:27:00,989
You cannot come with me. Go on.

971
01:27:02,189 --> 01:27:06,589
Coming back in time, changing history,
that's cheating.

972
01:27:09,089 --> 01:27:11,789
A trick I learned from an old friend.

973
01:27:20,189 --> 01:27:23,689
Live long and prosper.

974
01:27:42,989 --> 01:27:45,089
Mr. Scott?

975
01:27:49,589 --> 01:27:51,689
Mr. Scott, can you hear me?

976
01:27:59,389 --> 01:28:02,189
Hold on a second.

977
01:28:19,389 --> 01:28:20,589
No. No!

978
01:28:31,389 --> 01:28:32,489
RELEASE VALVE.

979
01:28:39,789 --> 01:28:42,589
Turbine release valve, activated.

980
01:28:49,089 --> 01:28:51,689
You all right? You all right?

981
01:28:53,689 --> 01:28:56,289
My head's buzzing and I'm soaked,
but otherwise I'm fine.

982
01:28:56,389 --> 01:29:01,689
Captain Spock, detecting unauthorized
access to water turbine control board

983
01:29:02,189 --> 01:29:03,889
Bring up the video.

984
01:29:07,689 --> 01:29:11,189
Security, seal the engineering deck.
We have intruders in turbine section 3.

985
01:29:12,389 --> 01:29:13,889
Set phasers to stun.

986
01:29:25,589 --> 01:29:27,089
Halt!

987
01:29:30,789 --> 01:29:32,089
Come with me

988
01:29:32,589 --> 01:29:34,589
cupcake!

989
01:29:41,989 --> 01:29:42,889
Who are you?

990
01:29:43,089 --> 01:29:43,954
- I am with him.
- He's with me.

991
01:29:43,989 --> 01:29:47,189
We are travelling at warp speed. How
did you manage to beam aboard this ship?

992
01:29:47,289 --> 01:29:48,554
You're the genius, you figure it out.

993
01:29:48,589 --> 01:29:51,689
As acting captain of this vessel
I order you to answer the question.

994
01:29:51,724 --> 01:29:53,989
Well I'm not telling, acting captain.

995
01:29:56,889 --> 01:30:01,089
What now? That doesn't frustrate you, does it? My
lack of cooperation, that doesn't make you angry?

996
01:30:01,189 --> 01:30:04,589
- Are you a member of Starfleet?
- Umm..yes. Can I get a towel?

997
01:30:04,689 --> 01:30:07,089
Under penalty of court martial I order
you to explain to me how you were able

998
01:30:07,189 --> 01:30:09,389
to beam aboard the ship while moving at warp

999
01:30:09,789 --> 01:30:10,889
- Well.
- Don't answer him.

1000
01:30:10,924 --> 01:30:13,089
You will answer me.

1001
01:30:14,389 --> 01:30:17,189
- I'd rather not take sides.
- What is it with you, Spock?

1002
01:30:19,689 --> 01:30:24,689
Your planet was just destroyed, your
mother murdered, and you're not even upset.

1003
01:30:24,789 --> 01:30:27,189
If you are presuming that these
experiences in any way impede

1004
01:30:27,289 --> 01:30:29,389
my ability to command this ship
you are mistaken.

1005
01:30:29,489 --> 01:30:32,989
And yet you were the one who said
fear was necessary for command.

1006
01:30:33,089 --> 01:30:36,289
I mean, did you his ship?
Did you see what he did?

1007
01:30:37,189 --> 01:30:39,289
- Yes, of course I did.
- So are you afraid or aren't you?

1008
01:30:39,389 --> 01:30:41,539
I will not allow you to lecture me
about the merits of emotion.

1009
01:30:41,574 --> 01:30:43,689
- Then why don't you stop me?
- Step away from me Mr. Kirk.

1010
01:30:43,789 --> 01:30:47,689
What is it like not to feel anger?
Or heartbreak?

1011
01:30:47,789 --> 01:30:51,089
Or the need to stop at nothing to avenge the
death of the woman who gave birth to you.

1012
01:30:51,189 --> 01:30:53,089
- Back away from me.
- You feel nothing!

1013
01:30:53,124 --> 01:30:55,589
It must not even compute for you.

1014
01:30:56,289 --> 01:30:57,989
You never loved her!

1015
01:31:22,389 --> 01:31:23,889
Spock.

1016
01:32:00,989 --> 01:32:03,689
Doctor, I am no longer fit for duty.

1017
01:32:03,789 --> 01:32:08,489
I relinquish my command based on the fact
that I have been emotionally compromised.

1018
01:32:09,589 --> 01:32:11,789
Please note the time and
date in the ship's log.

1019
01:32:38,889 --> 01:32:40,889
I like this ship.

1020
01:32:41,089 --> 01:32:42,689
You know it's exciting.

1021
01:32:45,189 --> 01:32:48,889
Well congratulations, Jim. Now we've got
no captain and no goddamn first officer

1022
01:32:48,989 --> 01:32:50,389
to replace him.

1023
01:32:51,889 --> 01:32:53,554
Yeah we do.

1024
01:32:53,589 --> 01:32:55,989
- What?
- Pike made him first officer.

1025
01:32:56,489 --> 01:32:59,189
- You've gotta be kidding me.
- Thanks for the support.

1026
01:33:02,389 --> 01:33:06,189
I sure hope you know what you're
doing, Captain.

1027
01:33:07,589 --> 01:33:09,489
So do I.

1028
01:33:13,789 --> 01:33:16,389
Attention, crew of the Enterprise,
this is James Kirk.

1029
01:33:17,789 --> 01:33:21,389
Mr. Spock has resigned commission
and advanced me to acting captain.

1030
01:33:22,589 --> 01:33:25,289
I know you're all expecting a regroup with the fleet,

1031
01:33:25,989 --> 01:33:28,154
but I'm ordering a pursuit course
of the enemy ship to Earth.

1032
01:33:28,189 --> 01:33:30,889
I want all departments at battle
stations and ready in 10 minutes.

1033
01:33:31,989 --> 01:33:36,189
Either we're going down or they are.

1034
01:33:36,989 --> 01:33:38,289
Kirk out.

1035
01:33:45,989 --> 01:33:48,289
Speak your mind Spock.

1036
01:33:50,889 --> 01:33:52,854
That would be unwise.

1037
01:33:52,889 --> 01:33:56,689
What is necessary is never unwise.

1038
01:33:58,189 --> 01:34:01,289
I am as conflicted as I once was as a child.

1039
01:34:02,989 --> 01:34:05,789
You will always be a child of two worlds.

1040
01:34:07,689 --> 01:34:10,389
I am grateful for this.

1041
01:34:11,489 --> 01:34:13,489
And for you.

1042
01:34:14,989 --> 01:34:18,189
I feel anger for the one who took mother's life.

1043
01:34:19,489 --> 01:34:22,389
An anger I cannot control.

1044
01:34:25,989 --> 01:34:31,289
I believe, as she would say...

1045
01:34:32,289 --> 01:34:35,089
...do not try to.

1046
01:34:35,489 --> 01:34:39,989
You asked me once why I married your mother.

1047
01:34:44,289 --> 01:34:47,089
I married her because I loved her.

1048
01:34:54,889 --> 01:34:57,289
Whatever the case we need to
get aboard Nero's ship undetected.

1049
01:34:57,324 --> 01:34:59,789
Just can't just go in there guns blazing, Jim.

1050
01:34:59,889 --> 01:35:01,654
I'm telling you to...

1051
01:35:01,689 --> 01:35:04,489
- Captain Kirk. Captain Kirk.
- Yes, Chekov. What is it?

1052
01:35:04,589 --> 01:35:06,389
Based on the Neradaâs course
from Vulcan

1053
01:35:06,489 --> 01:35:09,754
I have projected that Nero will
travel pass Saturn.

1054
01:35:09,789 --> 01:35:13,289
Like you said we need to stay
invisible to Nero or he'll destroy us.

1055
01:35:13,389 --> 01:35:15,889
If Mr. Scott can get us to warp factor 4

1056
01:35:15,989 --> 01:35:20,289
and if we drop out of warp behind one
of Saturn's moons, say Titan.

1057
01:35:20,389 --> 01:35:22,989
The magnetic distortion from
the planet's rings

1058
01:35:23,089 --> 01:35:25,454
will make us invisible to Nero's sensors.

1059
01:35:25,489 --> 01:35:27,889
From there, as long as the drill
is not activated

1060
01:35:27,989 --> 01:35:29,589
we can beam aboard the enemy ship.

1061
01:35:29,624 --> 01:35:31,389
Aye, that might work.

1062
01:35:31,989 --> 01:35:34,389
- Wait a minute kid, how old are you?
- 17, sir.

1063
01:35:35,089 --> 01:35:36,389
Oh good, he's 17.

1064
01:35:36,424 --> 01:35:38,054
Doctor.

1065
01:35:38,089 --> 01:35:41,589
Mr. Chekov is correct. I can
confirm his telemetry.

1066
01:35:41,989 --> 01:35:44,054
If Mr. Sulu is able to maneuver us into position

1067
01:35:44,089 --> 01:35:46,789
I can beam aboard Nero's ship,
steal back the black hole device

1068
01:35:46,889 --> 01:35:49,289
and if possible bring back Captain Pike.

1069
01:35:49,689 --> 01:35:51,589
I won't allow you to do that Mr. Spock.

1070
01:35:52,389 --> 01:35:55,089
Romulans and Vulcans
share a common ancestry.

1071
01:35:55,589 --> 01:35:59,189
Our cultural similarities will make it easier
for me to access the ship's computer

1072
01:35:59,289 --> 01:36:00,589
to locate the device.

1073
01:36:02,189 --> 01:36:06,189
Also my mother was human. Which
makes Earth the only home I have left.

1074
01:36:13,589 --> 01:36:15,489
I'm coming with you.

1075
01:36:15,789 --> 01:36:18,989
I would cite regulation, but
I know you will simply ignore it.

1076
01:36:21,689 --> 01:36:24,789
See? We are getting to know each other.

1077
01:36:40,089 --> 01:36:42,189
Prepare the drill.

1078
01:36:57,689 --> 01:37:03,489
All stop in 3... 2... 1.

1079
01:37:08,589 --> 01:37:11,489
Give me 1/4 impulse burst for 5 seconds.

1080
01:37:11,589 --> 01:37:13,489
I'll do the rest with thrusters.
On my mark.

1081
01:37:13,524 --> 01:37:14,489
Aye.

1082
01:37:15,189 --> 01:37:16,189
Fire.

1083
01:37:42,989 --> 01:37:45,489
Transporter room. We are in
position above Titan.

1084
01:37:45,889 --> 01:37:48,589
Really? Fine job Mr. Sulu, well done.

1085
01:37:49,189 --> 01:37:52,389
- How are we Scotty?
- Unbelievably sir. The ship is in position.

1086
01:37:56,389 --> 01:38:00,289
Whatever happens Mr. Sulu, if you
think you have the tactical advantage

1087
01:38:00,389 --> 01:38:03,489
you fire on that ship even if we're still
on board. That's an order.

1088
01:38:05,989 --> 01:38:06,954
Yes, sir.

1089
01:38:06,989 --> 01:38:09,789
Otherwise we'll contact the Enterprise
when we're ready to be beamed back.

1090
01:38:10,889 --> 01:38:12,989
Good luck.

1091
01:38:25,089 --> 01:38:27,989
- I will be back.
- You better be.

1092
01:38:29,389 --> 01:38:33,289
- I'll be monitoring your frequency.
- Thank you, Nyota.

1093
01:38:49,689 --> 01:38:52,389
- So her first name's Nyota?
- I have no comment on the matter.

1094
01:38:52,489 --> 01:38:55,639
Oky doky then. If thereâs any common
sense in the design of the enemy's ship

1095
01:38:55,674 --> 01:38:58,789
I should be putting you somewhere in the
cargo bay, shouldn't be a soul in sight.

1096
01:38:59,189 --> 01:39:00,289
Energize.

1097
01:39:43,689 --> 01:39:46,289
Captain, we have Starfleet officers
aboard the ship.

1098
01:39:46,389 --> 01:39:48,989
- One of them is Vulcan.
- No.

1099
01:39:53,489 --> 01:39:55,289
Ayel!

1100
01:40:09,189 --> 01:40:11,589
- I'll cover ya.
- Are you certain?

1101
01:40:11,624 --> 01:40:13,089
Yeah, I've gotcha.

1102
01:40:32,789 --> 01:40:36,189
Do you know where it is?
The black hole device?

1103
01:40:37,989 --> 01:40:40,089
And Captain Pike.

1104
01:41:02,189 --> 01:41:03,289
Move.

1105
01:41:04,189 --> 01:41:06,189
They have activated the drill.

1106
01:41:07,189 --> 01:41:08,789
Communication and transportation are inoperative.

1107
01:41:08,889 --> 01:41:10,389
Sulu, please tell me you have them.

1108
01:41:10,489 --> 01:41:12,089
Otherwise we won't be
able to beam them back.

1109
01:41:12,124 --> 01:41:13,989
Kirk and Spock are on their own now.

1110
01:41:33,189 --> 01:41:36,789
I foresee a complication. The design of this ship
is far more advanced than I have anticipated.

1111
01:41:37,189 --> 01:41:39,989
Voice print and face recognition
analysis enabled.

1112
01:41:40,289 --> 01:41:42,389
Welcome back Ambassador Spock.

1113
01:41:42,489 --> 01:41:43,889
That's weird.

1114
01:41:45,289 --> 01:41:48,089
Computer, what is your manufacturing origin?

1115
01:41:48,289 --> 01:41:52,789
Stardate 2387. Commissioned by the
Vulcan Science Academy.

1116
01:41:55,789 --> 01:41:57,989
It appears that you have been keeping
important information from me.

1117
01:41:58,089 --> 01:42:00,189
You'll be able to fly this thing, right?

1118
01:42:00,224 --> 01:42:01,989
Something tells me I already have.

1119
01:42:03,289 --> 01:42:05,089
- Good luck.
- Jim.

1120
01:42:06,189 --> 01:42:09,689
The statistical likelihood that our
plan will succeed is less than 4.3%.

1121
01:42:09,789 --> 01:42:10,354
I will work.

1122
01:42:10,389 --> 01:42:12,589
In the event that I don't return
please tell Lt. Uhura...

1123
01:42:12,689 --> 01:42:14,589
Spock, it'll work.

1124
01:42:25,289 --> 01:42:26,689
Fascinating.

1125
01:42:35,189 --> 01:42:37,889
Startup sequence initiated.

1126
01:43:21,689 --> 01:43:24,289
Nero, order your men to disable
the drill or I will...

1127
01:43:34,389 --> 01:43:37,389
I know your face from Earth's history.

1128
01:44:22,489 --> 01:44:24,989
James T. Kirk was considered
to be a great man.

1129
01:44:25,889 --> 01:44:29,789
He went on to captain the USS
Enterprise. But that was another life.

1130
01:44:30,689 --> 01:44:33,389
A life I will deprive you of just like
I did your father.

1131
01:45:06,389 --> 01:45:10,189
Captain Nero. The Vulcan ship's has been
taken. The drill has been destroyed.

1132
01:45:10,989 --> 01:45:15,289
Spock! Spock!

1133
01:45:33,089 --> 01:45:34,889
- Open a channel.
- Yes, sir.

1134
01:45:36,189 --> 01:45:39,389
Spock, I knew I should have
killed you when I had the chance.

1135
01:45:39,489 --> 01:45:41,489
I hereby confiscate this illegally
obtained ship

1136
01:45:41,524 --> 01:45:43,489
and order you to surrender your
vessel. No terms.

1137
01:45:43,589 --> 01:45:45,054
That ship... take it out.

1138
01:45:45,089 --> 01:45:48,189
- Sir, if you ignite the red matter..
- I want the Spock dead now!

1139
01:46:03,889 --> 01:46:05,689
- He went to warp.
- Go after him.

1140
01:46:05,724 --> 01:46:06,689
Yes, sir.

1141
01:46:37,089 --> 01:46:39,589
Your species is even weaker
than I expected.

1142
01:46:43,589 --> 01:46:45,489
You can't even speak.

1143
01:46:47,689 --> 01:46:48,889
What?

1144
01:46:49,389 --> 01:46:51,689
I got your gun.

1145
01:47:17,689 --> 01:47:18,989
What's he doing?

1146
01:47:19,089 --> 01:47:22,089
Ambassador Spock, you are
on a collision course.

1147
01:47:22,489 --> 01:47:24,189
Fire everything!

1148
01:47:30,889 --> 01:47:34,989
Incoming missiles. If the ship is hit,
the red matter will be ignited.

1149
01:47:35,189 --> 01:47:36,989
Understood.

1150
01:47:42,989 --> 01:47:44,489
Captain, I've picked up another ship.

1151
01:48:06,089 --> 01:48:08,589
- What are you doing here?
- Following orders.

1152
01:48:29,289 --> 01:48:31,189
Enterprise now!

1153
01:48:53,789 --> 01:48:55,489
Nice timing Scotty.

1154
01:48:56,389 --> 01:48:58,589
Haha! I've never beamed three people
from two targets

1155
01:48:58,689 --> 01:49:00,189
onto one pad before.

1156
01:49:00,489 --> 01:49:02,989
- Jim. - Bones.
- I've got him.

1157
01:49:06,189 --> 01:49:08,089
That was pretty good.

1158
01:49:08,689 --> 01:49:11,789
Captain, the enemy ship is loosing
power. They're shields are down.

1159
01:49:11,989 --> 01:49:13,889
- Hail them now.
- Aye.

1160
01:49:49,289 --> 01:49:51,989
This is Captain James T. Kirk
of the USS Enterprise.

1161
01:49:52,589 --> 01:49:55,189
Your ship is compromised. You're
too close to the singularity

1162
01:49:55,289 --> 01:49:58,289
to survive without assistance
which we are willing to provide.

1163
01:50:01,489 --> 01:50:03,289
Captain, what are you doing?

1164
01:50:03,389 --> 01:50:05,889
Showing them compassion may be the only way
to make peace with Romulus, Spock.

1165
01:50:05,924 --> 01:50:08,889
It's logical, Spock.
Thought you'd like that.

1166
01:50:09,389 --> 01:50:11,989
No, not really. Not this time.

1167
01:50:12,089 --> 01:50:16,289
I would rather suffer the end of
Romulus a thousand times,

1168
01:50:16,389 --> 01:50:20,789
I would rather die in agony than
accept assistance from you.

1169
01:50:20,889 --> 01:50:22,089
You got it.

1170
01:50:22,789 --> 01:50:25,089
Arm phasers. Fire everything we've got.

1171
01:50:25,124 --> 01:50:26,089
Yes, sir.

1172
01:51:10,989 --> 01:51:13,089
- Sulu, let's go home.
- Yes, sir.

1173
01:51:24,289 --> 01:51:26,589
- Why aren't we at warp?
- We are, sir.

1174
01:51:26,789 --> 01:51:28,989
Kirk to engineering.
Get us out of here, Scotty.

1175
01:51:29,024 --> 01:51:30,989
You bet your ass Captain!

1176
01:51:34,089 --> 01:51:36,189
Captain, we're caught in
the gravity well. It's got us.

1177
01:51:36,224 --> 01:51:37,754
Go to maximum warp. Push it!

1178
01:51:37,789 --> 01:51:39,789
I'm giving it all she's got Captain.

1179
01:51:49,089 --> 01:51:51,589
All she's got isn't good enough.
What else you got?

1180
01:51:51,624 --> 01:51:53,889
Ok, if we eject the core and detonate

1181
01:51:53,989 --> 01:51:56,789
the blast could be enough to push us away.
I can't promise anything though.

1182
01:52:00,089 --> 01:52:01,989
Do it! Do it! Do it!

1183
01:52:02,689 --> 01:52:04,489
- Clear the area. Go!
- Yes, sir.

1184
01:53:32,089 --> 01:53:33,489
Father?

1185
01:53:42,089 --> 01:53:44,689
I am not our father.

1186
01:53:51,589 --> 01:53:56,189
There are so few Vulcans left we
cannot afford to ignore each other.

1187
01:53:59,289 --> 01:54:02,189
Then why did you send Kirk aboard when
you alone could have explained the truth?

1188
01:54:02,289 --> 01:54:04,254
Because you needed each other.

1189
01:54:04,289 --> 01:54:08,589
I could not deprive you of the revelation
of all that you can accomplish together.

1190
01:54:08,689 --> 01:54:11,889
Of a friendship that will define you both.

1191
01:54:12,089 --> 01:54:14,289
In ways you cannot yet realize.

1192
01:54:15,689 --> 01:54:18,189
How'd you persuade him to
keep your secret?

1193
01:54:18,289 --> 01:54:21,489
He inferred that universe
ending paradoxes would ensue

1194
01:54:21,589 --> 01:54:23,189
should he break his promise.

1195
01:54:23,224 --> 01:54:24,889
You lied?

1196
01:54:25,889 --> 01:54:28,989
- Oh. I implied.
- A gamble?

1197
01:54:29,089 --> 01:54:30,854
An act of faith.

1198
01:54:30,889 --> 01:54:34,389
One I hope you will repeat in
the future in Starfleet.

1199
01:54:34,589 --> 01:54:37,889
In the face of extinction it is only
logical I resign my Starfleet commission

1200
01:54:37,989 --> 01:54:39,054
and help rebuild our race.

1201
01:54:39,089 --> 01:54:41,689
And yet you can be in two places at once.

1202
01:54:42,689 --> 01:54:44,889
I urge you to remain in Starfleet.

1203
01:54:45,789 --> 01:54:49,489
I've already located a suitable planet
on which to establish a Vulcan colony.

1204
01:54:50,089 --> 01:54:53,989
Spock, in this case do yourself a favor

1205
01:54:55,389 --> 01:54:58,789
put aside logic, do what feels right.

1206
01:55:04,889 --> 01:55:08,089
Since my customary farewell
would appear oddly self serving

1207
01:55:08,389 --> 01:55:11,389
I shall simply say good luck.

1208
01:55:23,089 --> 01:55:26,489
This assembly calls Captain
James Tiberius Kirk.

1209
01:55:27,389 --> 01:55:30,589
Your inspirational valor and supreme
dedication to your comrades

1210
01:55:30,689 --> 01:55:32,989
is in keeping with the highest
traditions of service.

1211
01:55:33,789 --> 01:55:38,289
And reflect at most credit to yourself,
your crew and the Federation.

1212
01:55:39,489 --> 01:55:42,589
It is my honor to award you
with this commendation.

1213
01:55:46,889 --> 01:55:51,589
By Starfleet order 28455, you are
hereby directed to report to Admiral Pike

1214
01:55:51,889 --> 01:55:55,489
USS Enterprise, for duty as his relief.

1215
01:56:03,789 --> 01:56:05,289
I relieve you, sir.

1216
01:56:06,089 --> 01:56:08,089
I am relieved.

1217
01:56:09,789 --> 01:56:12,389
- Thank you, sir.
- Congratulations, Captain.

1218
01:56:14,189 --> 01:56:16,389
Your father would be proud of you.

1219
01:56:45,789 --> 01:56:47,489
Thrusters on full.

1220
01:56:47,889 --> 01:56:50,589
Manouvering thrusters and impulse
engines at your command, sir.

1221
01:56:50,689 --> 01:56:53,389
Weapon systems and shields on standby.

1222
01:56:53,589 --> 01:56:56,289
Dock control reports ready, Captain.

1223
01:57:00,489 --> 01:57:01,589
Bones.

1224
01:57:02,589 --> 01:57:04,289
Buckle up.

1225
01:57:07,789 --> 01:57:09,489
Scotty, how we doin'?

1226
01:57:09,589 --> 01:57:11,989
Dilithium chambers at maximum Captain.

1227
01:57:13,289 --> 01:57:15,089
Get down!

1228
01:57:16,889 --> 01:57:19,789
Mr. Sulu, prepare to engage thrusters.

1229
01:57:22,689 --> 01:57:24,489
Permission to come aboard, Captain.

1230
01:57:25,489 --> 01:57:27,189
Permission granted.

1231
01:57:27,989 --> 01:57:30,089
As you have yet to select a first officer,

1232
01:57:30,189 --> 01:57:32,589
respectfully I would like to submit
my candidacy.

1233
01:57:33,689 --> 01:57:36,389
Should you desire I can provide
character references.

1234
01:57:37,689 --> 01:57:39,689
It would be my honor Commander.

1235
01:57:43,589 --> 01:57:45,689
Maneuvering thrusters Mr. Sulu.

1236
01:57:48,089 --> 01:57:50,589
- Thrusters on standby.
- Take us out.

1237
01:57:51,189 --> 01:57:52,489
Aye aye, Captain.

1238
01:57:57,189 --> 01:58:00,389
SPACE, THE FINAL FRONTIER

1239
01:58:02,089 --> 01:58:05,589
THESE ARE THE VOYAGES OF
THE STARSHIP ENTERPRISE

1240
01:58:06,689 --> 01:58:10,489
HER ONGOING MISSION: TO
EXPLORE STRANGE NEW WORLDS,

1241
01:58:11,289 --> 01:58:14,889
TO SEEK OUT NEW LIFE FORMS
AND NEW CIVILISATIONS

1242
01:58:15,589 --> 01:58:20,089
TO BOLDLY GO WHERE NOONE
HAS GONE BEFORE.

